n#|3|at|^^That's the really crucial question, because you need to have a plan.  This contract is at most -1 (losing 1 trick in each side suit) but you really need to try to make it, because some NS pairs might buy the contract in 4@H, and some EW pairs might push on to 5@S, which is probably going to be off as we know the @CK is onside.|
pg| ***** 16 ***** |


---------------------------------------------------------------------------
